<p>&nbsp;Squadron Capital focuses on delivering fast and confidential liquidity through non-recourse financing structures. These facilities are designed without requiring personal or corporate guarantees, allowing shareholders and listed companies to access funding while maintaining financial flexibility. Financing is available in multiple currencies, including USD, EUR, SGD, and other preferred currencies, with no restrictions on how the capital can be used. Every transaction is handled with strict confidentiality, ensuring privacy for all parties involved.</p>
<p>&nbsp;The company distinguishes itself by offering a transparent funding process with no upfront costs. Clients are not required to pay application fees, processing fees, or any advance charges before financing is provided. Capital is committed before the transaction closes, enabling all parties to verify that funds are available before any shares are transferred. All financing terms are finalized and agreed upon in advance through a formal facility agreement, providing certainty before the transaction proceeds. As a direct funding source, Squadron Capital deploys its own capital rather than relying on intermediaries or third-party funding approvals, allowing for faster execution once terms have been accepted.</p>
<p>&nbsp;Over the years, Squadron Capital has facilitated numerous equity-backed transactions across Asia-Pacific's leading financial markets. The firm's long-standing regional presence and experience have enabled it to establish strong relationships within the financial industry while paying millions in referral compensation to qualified intermediaries throughout its operating history. Its expertise spans major stock exchanges, including the Hong Kong Stock Exchange (HKEX), Singapore Exchange (SGX), Tokyo Stock Exchange (TSE), Australian Securities Exchange (ASX), Stock Exchange of Thailand (SET), Indonesia Stock Exchange (IDX), Bursa Malaysia, and several other regional markets.</p>
<p>&nbsp;The company is supported by an advisory board composed of respected leaders from banking, regulatory, and political sectors across its key operating markets. Their strategic guidance strengthens Squadron Capital's institutional credibility and supports the firm's commitment to delivering reliable financing solutions throughout the region.</p>
<p>&nbsp;Financial professionals such as private bankers and financial advisors can participate in Squadron Capital's referral program by introducing qualified equity financing opportunities ranging from US$1 million to US$100 million. The program offers competitive referral compensation, streamlined processing, and comprehensive support from dedicated relationship managers throughout every stage of the transaction. Referral partners benefit from rapid underwriting, prompt compensation upon successful funding, and access to flexible capital solutions across multiple international markets.</p>
<p>&nbsp;The funding process is designed to be straightforward and efficient. It begins with the secure submission of a financing opportunity, followed by confidential consultations with the funding recipient. After a rapid underwriting review, a term sheet is issued outlining the agreed financing conditions. Once approved, funding is deployed in the recipient's preferred currency and jurisdiction. Upon successful completion of the financing facility, referral compensation is processed promptly for eligible financial professionals.</p>
